Former FBI Director Louis Freeh was involved in a car crash near his summer home in Barnard, Vermont last summer .
He nearly died in just 60 seconds if it weren't for the quick response from paramedics and an FBI agent on the scene .
Now, James Comey and Vermont Senator Patrick Leahy spoke about the accident for the first time last week .
'Louis would have died within a minute or so. They stopped the bleeding,' said Leahy .